Uganda Freezes $375 Million of Libyan Assets After UN Ruling, Monitor Says

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-03-25T05:02:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/uganda-freezes-375-million-of-libyan-assets-after-un-ruling-monitor-says.html
Uganda  will freeze all Libyan
government investments worth $375 million as it enforces United
Nations sanctions against the North African nation, the Daily
Monitor reported, citing the Foreign Ministry.  The East African nation is awaiting guidelines from UN
Secretary General Ban Ki-moon after it wrote to him seeking
details regarding the implementation of the sanctions, the
Kampala-based newspaper reported, citing Henry Okello Oryem,
minister of state for foreign affairs.  Libya â€™s government has investments in Uganda Telcom Ltd.,
National Housing and Construction Corp., Laico Lake Victoria
Hotel, Tropical Bank Ltd., Tamoil East Africa Ltd. and OilLibya
Co., the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
